title: My love mine all mine
lyrics: Moon, a hole of light through the big top tent up high Here before and after me shining down on me Moon, tell me if I could send up my heart to you So, when I die, which I must do. Could it shine down here with you? 'Cause my love is mine, all mine I love, my, my, mine Nothing in the world belongs to me But my love, mine, all mine, all mine My baby here on Earth showed me what my heart was worth So, when it comes to be my turn. Could you shine it down here for her? 'Cause my love is mine, all mine I love, my, my, mine Nothing in the world be longs to me But my love, mine, all mine Nothing in the world is mine for free But my love, mine, all mine, all mine
